## End-to-end capability tests

If this project has an `e2e/` directory with `e2e/testing/*-test.md` files, those are spec-driven capability tests
following the methodology in the `/e2e-runbooks` skill. Before adding a new one, run the skill. Each
capability test is a triple: immutable `e2e/testing/{N}-{capability}-test.md` spec, immutable
`e2e/testing/{N}-{capability}-tasks.template.md` checklist, and one timestamped run record per execution under
`e2e/testing/runs/`. Assertions are observable behaviour only (HTTP status, response body, persisted state); never log
substrings.

Projects on OpenSpec can install the matching schema for slash-command lifecycle integration. See
[openspec-schemas/e2e-runbooks](https://github.com/Lukk17/openspec-schemas/tree/master/e2e-runbooks).

